  "prompt": "\"CAS PRES CHQ\" what does this SBI statement message mean?",
  "response": "The message \"CAS PRES CHQ\" on an SBI (State Bank of India) statement typically refers to a \"Cash Presentment Cheque.\" This means that a cheque has been presented for encashment or deposit against the account. It indicates that funds are being processed in relation to a cheque transaction. If you have further questions about specific transactions, it's always a good idea to contact your bank directly for clarification.",
